Package almost.functional

Functional classes and interfaces of Almost Functional.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
BiFunction<F,S,R> An interface of a function that accepts a first and second argument and returns a result.
Consumer<T> A functional interface that consumes, without results, an argument.
Function<A,R> A functional interface and can be used to apply a function to a type and yield a result.
Predicate<T> A functional interface that can be used to indicate a boolean test is to be applied to some type.
Supplier<T> A supplier of results.
 

Class Summary
Optional<T> A container object which may or may not contain a non-null value.
Predicates Utility operations on predicates.
 

Package almost.functional Description

Functional classes and interfaces of Almost Functional. These are designed as a bare minimum set of functionality for JDKs prior to 1.8.
